[223.028792, "o", "  ACT 4: Critical Review\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n\r\n"]
[225.030249, "o", "$ claude -p \"Review all artifacts in this project for errors, omissions, and mischaracterizations: docs/helix/01-frame/prd.md, docs/helix/01-frame/user-stories/US-001-temperature-conversion.md, docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-001-temperature-conversion.md, tests/convert.test.js, and bin/convert.js. Does the implementation match the specs? Are acceptance criteria covered? Be concise — list findings as bullet points.\"\r\n\r\n"]
[258.41891, "o", "## Review Findings\r\n\r\n### Errors\r\n- None found. The conversion formulas are correct, CLI arg parsing matches the TD spec, and `toFixed(1)` satisfies F3.\r\n\r\n### Omissions\r\n\r\n- **Test coverage is thin.** Only 3 unit tests for the pure functions. No tests for:\r\n  - `toFahrenheit` with non-zero input (e.g., 100 → 212)\r\n  - Negative temperatures (e.g., -40, the crossover point)\r\n  - Boundary/large values\r\n- **No CLI integration tests.** PRD requires exit code 0 on success and non-zero on invalid input. TD specifies behavior for missing flag, non-numeric temp, and both-flags-provided — none of these are tested.\r\n- **User story AC is minimal.** US-001 only has 2 acceptance criteria (one per direction). It doesn't cover error cases that the PRD explicitly requires (non-zero exit on invalid input) or the output format constraint (F3). These PRD requirements have no traceability back to user-story-level ACs.\r\n- **PRD mentions `hello-helix convert` command** (lines 17, 27) implying a `convert` subcommand via a `hello-helix` binary, but `package.json` `bin` field isn't verified here — the TD only references `node bin/convert.js`. If `package.json` doesn't map `hello-helix` to `bin/convert.js`, the PRD examples won't work as written.\r\n\r\n### Mischaracterizations\r\n- **PRD examples use `hello-helix convert --to-celsius`** with a `convert` subcommand, but the implementation and TD use `node bin/convert.js --to-celsius` with no subcommand parsing. The CLI doesn't recognize or require a `convert` subcommand — passing one would actually be silently ignored (it's not `--to-celsius` or `--to-fahrenheit`, so the loop skips it). This is a spec/implementation mismatch, though functionally harmless if invoked via the `bin` field.\r\n\r\n### Summary\r\nThe core logic is correct and the two happy-path ACs pass. The main gaps are: (1) no CLI/error-path test coverage for explicitly specified PRD and TD behaviors, (2) the PRD's `hello-helix convert` invocation style isn't reflected in the implementation, and (3) the user story doesn't trace error-handling or output-format requirements.\r\n"]
[258.571139, "o", "\r\n"]
[263.573821, "o", "\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n  ACT 5: Queue Health & Triage\r\n━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\r\n\r\n"]
[265.575232, "o", "$ claude -p \"Read tests/convert.test.js and bin/convert.js. List the gaps: which error-handling code paths have no tests? Which conversion edge cases are untested? Which acceptance criteria lack integration tests? Output a numbered list of gaps — one line each, no explanation.\"\r\n\r\n"]
[279.726854, "o", "1. No test for `toFahrenheit` with negative input (e.g., -40°C → -40.0°F)\r\n2. No test for `toCelsius` with negative input (e.g., -40°F → -40.0°C)\r\n3. No test for `toFahrenheit` with non-zero positive input (e.g., 100°C → 212°F)\r\n4. No test for non-numeric input to `toFahrenheit` or `toCelsius` (NaN, string, undefined)\r\n5. No CLI integration test: missing flag prints usage to stderr and exits 1\r\n6. No CLI integration test: non-finite temperature (e.g., \"abc\") prints error to stderr and exits 1\r\n7. No CLI integration test: `--to-celsius <temp>` produces correct stdout output\r\n8. No CLI integration test: `--to-fahrenheit <temp>` produces correct stdout output\r\n9. No CLI integration test: missing value after flag (e.g., `--to-celsius` with no number)\r\n10. No test for decimal precision — output must be `.toFixed(1)`\r\n11. No test for very large or very small temperature values (overflow/boundary)\r\n12. No test that `toFahrenheit` with body-temp equivalent (37°C → 98.6°F) mirrors existing `toCelsius` test\r\n"]
[279.90058, "o", "\r\n"]
